[debug] [2026-03-09T14:03:35.313Z] <<< [apiv2][status] POST https://cloudaicompanion.googleapis.com/v1beta/projects/horti-gestao/locations/global/instances/default:completeTask 200
[debug] [2026-03-09T14:03:35.313Z] <<< [apiv2][body] POST https://cloudaicompanion.googleapis.com/v1beta/projects/horti-gestao/locations/global/instances/default:completeTask {"output":{"messages":[{"content":"It's great you're diving into creating operations with Firebase Data Connect! Let's craft some GraphQL operations for your app based on the provided schema, keeping authentication and best practices in mind.\n\nHere are four operations designed for common use cases, each with appropriate `@auth` directives:\n\n```graphql\n# Operation 1: Get a user's active subscriptions\nquery GetUserActiveSubscriptions($userId: UUID!) @auth(level: USER, insecureReason: \"This operation is safe to expose to all logged in users. The userId can be used to filter results.\") {\n  userSubscriptions(where: {\n    userId: { eq: $userId },\n    isCanceled: { eq: false }\n  }) {\n    id\n    name\n    cost\n    billingCycle\n    renewalDate\n    subscriptionType {\n      name\n      description\n    }\n    reminders_on_userSubscription(where: { isSent: { eq: false } }) {\n      id\n      message\n      reminderDate\n    }\n  }\n}\n\n# Operation 2: Create a new reminder for a user's subscription\nmutation CreateReminderForUserSubscription($userSubscriptionId: UUID!, $message: String!, $reminderDate: Date!) @auth(level: USER) {\n  reminder_insert(data: {\n    userSubscriptionId: $userSubscriptionId,\n    userId_expr: \"auth.uid\", # Ensures the reminder is associated with the authenticated user\n    message: $message,\n    reminderDate: $reminderDate,\n    isSent: false,\n    createdAt_expr: \"request.time\"\n  })\n}\n\n# Operation 3: Mark a reminder as sent\nmutation MarkReminderAsSent($reminderId: UUID!) @auth(level: USER) {\n  reminder_update(\n    key: { id: $reminderId },\n    data: {\n      isSent: true,\n      sentAt_expr: \"request.time\"\n    }\n  )\n}\n\n# Operation 4: Get a list of all available subscription types (publicly accessible for exploration)\nquery GetAllSubscriptionTypes @auth(level: PUBLIC, insecureReason: \"This operation is safe to expose to the public\") {\n  subscriptionTypes {\n    id\n    name\n    description\n  }\n}\n```\n\nThese operations cover:\n\n1.  **`GetUserActiveSubscriptions`**: This query fetches all active subscriptions for a specific user, including their associated subscription type details and any unsent reminders. It uses `auth.uid` implicitly (via the `$userId` variable, assuming you'll pass `auth.uid` from the client) to filter results, making it secure for logged-in users.\n2.  **`CreateReminderForUserSubscription`**: This mutation allows a logged-in user to create a new reminder for one of their subscriptions. It securely links the reminder to the current user using `userId_expr: \"auth.uid\"` and sets the creation timestamp.\n3.  **`MarkReminderAsSent`**: This mutation allows a logged-in user to update the status of a reminder, marking it as sent. It also records the `sentAt` timestamp.\n4.  **`GetAllSubscriptionTypes`**: This query is publicly accessible and retrieves all defined subscription types, which might be useful for users browsing available options before subscribing. It has a clear `insecureReason` as it doesn't expose any sensitive user data.\n\nTo explore this further, you might consider asking:\n\n*   How can I add more complex authorization rules to these operations, for example, allowing only administrators to create new `SubscriptionType` entries?\n*   Can you show me an example of how to update a user's subscription details, like changing its name or cost?\n*   How would I implement a query to find all subscriptions renewing within the next 30 days for the current user?","author":"model"}]},"outputDataContext":{"additionalContext":{"@type":"type.googleapis.com/google.cloud.cloudaicompanion.v1main.ChatOutputDataContext","relatedContent":{}}},"attributionContext":{"citationMetadata":{}}}
[debug] [2026-03-09T14:03:37.140Z] <<< [apiv2][status] POST https://cloudaicompanion.googleapis.com/v1beta/projects/horti-gestao/locations/global/instances/default:completeTask 200
[debug] [2026-03-09T14:03:37.140Z] <<< [apiv2][body] POST https://cloudaicompanion.googleapis.com/v1beta/projects/horti-gestao/locations/global/instances/default:completeTask {"output":{"messages":[{"content":"To populate your database with seed data, I'll create a mutation that inserts sample `SubscriptionType` and `User` entries, and then associates a `UserSubscription` and a `Reminder` with them. Since this is seed data, I'll use hardcoded literals rather than variables. This mutation will run as a transaction to ensure all or nothing is committed.\n\n```graphql\nmutation CreateSeedData @transaction @auth(level: USER, insecureReason: \"This is a seed data mutation, only to be run by an administrator.\") {\n  subscriptionType_insertMany(data: [\n    {\n      id: \"a0eebc99-9c0b-4ef8-bb6d-6bb9bd380a11\",\n      name: \"Premium\",\n      description: \"Access to all premium features.\"\n    },\n    {\n      id: \"b1eebc99-9c0b-4ef8-bb6d-6bb9bd380a22\",\n      name: \"Basic\",\n      description: \"Standard features.\"\n    }\n  ]) {\n    id\n  }\n  user_insertMany(data: [\n    {\n      id: \"c2eebc99-9c0b-4ef8-bb6d-6bb9bd380a33\",\n      displayName: \"John Doe\",\n      email: \"john.doe@example.com\",\n      createdAt: \"2023-01-01T10:00:00Z\"\n    },\n    {\n      id: \"d3eebc99-9c0b-4ef8-bb6d-6bb9bd380a44\",\n      displayName: \"Jane Smith\",\n      email: \"jane.smith@example.com\",\n      createdAt: \"2023-01-05T12:30:00Z\"\n    }\n  ]) {\n    id\n  }\n  userSubscription_insertMany(data: [\n    {\n      id: \"e4eebc99-9c0b-4ef8-bb6d-6bb9bd380a55\",\n      userId: \"c2eebc99-9c0b-4ef8-bb6d-6bb9bd380a33\",\n      subscriptionTypeId: \"a0eebc99-9c0b-4ef8-bb6d-6bb9bd380a11\",\n      name: \"John's Premium Subscription\",\n      cost: 9.99,\n      billingCycle: \"Monthly\",\n      renewalDate: \"2024-07-01\",\n      createdAt: \"2023-06-01T08:00:00Z\"\n    },\n    {\n      id: \"f5eebc99-9c0b-4ef8-bb6d-6bb9bd380a66\",\n      userId: \"d3eebc99-9c0b-4ef8-bb6d-6bb9bd380a44\",\n      subscriptionTypeId: \"b1eebc99-9c0b-4ef8-bb6d-6bb9bd380a22\",\n      name: \"Jane's Basic Subscription\",\n      cost: 4.99,\n      billingCycle: \"Annually\",\n      renewalDate: \"2024-10-01\",\n      createdAt: \"2023-10-01T14:15:00Z\"\n    }\n  ]) {\n    id\n  }\n  reminder_insertMany(data: [\n    {\n      id: \"g6eebc99-9c0b-4ef8-bb6d-6bb9bd380a77\",\n      userId: \"c2eebc99-9c0b-4ef8-bb6d-6bb9bd380a33\",\n      userSubscriptionId: \"e4eebc99-9c0b-4ef8-bb6d-6bb9bd380a55\",\n      reminderDate: \"2024-06-25\",\n      message: \"Subscription renewal for John's Premium.\",\n      isSent: false,\n      createdAt: \"2024-06-20T09:00:00Z\"\n    },\n    {\n      id: \"h7eebc99-9c0b-4ef8-bb6d-6bb9bd380a88\",\n      userId: \"d3eebc99-9c0b-4ef8-bb6d-6bb9bd380a44\",\n      userSubscriptionId: \"f5eebc99-9c0b-4ef8-bb6d-6bb9bd380a66\",\n      reminderDate: \"2024-09-20\",\n      message: \"Subscription renewal for Jane's Basic.\",\n      isSent: false,\n      createdAt: \"2024-09-15T11:00:00Z\"\n    }\n  ]) {\n    id\n  }\n}\n```","author":"model"}]},"outputDataContext":{"additionalContext":{"@type":"type.googleapis.com/google.cloud.cloudaicompanion.v1main.ChatOutputDataContext","relatedContent":{}}},"attributionContext":{"citationMetadata":{}}}
